</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[138,1185,886,942]" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis box="[138,252,886,910]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Paramere slender; distal part longer than basal one, apically slightly broadened in lateral view, with 
<emphasis box="[377,401,919,942]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">ca</emphasis>
five or six minute sensilla on distal margin (
<figureCitation box="[924,1051,918,942]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="11.[130,190,853,872]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,817]" captionTargetId="figure-184@11.[170,1128,133,817]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 3. Amiota (Amiota) xishuangbanna Chen and Aotsuka, sp. nov. „ (see Figure 2 for further explanation)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657902/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">Figure 3D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[138,259,999,1023]" box="[138,259,999,1023]" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis box="[138,259,999,1023]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[138,1185,1048,1104]" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis box="[138,226,1048,1072]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">Thorax.</emphasis>
Thorax yellow, with dull, brown patches and stripes; scutellum yellow, brown on margin; pleura brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[138,1185,1145,1203]" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis box="[138,206,1145,1169]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">Wing.</emphasis>
Ventral surface of costal vein with 
<emphasis box="[618,642,1145,1168]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">ca</emphasis>
14–15 distinct, peg-like spinules between R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1152,1185,1154,1171]" fontSize="7" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">2+3</subScript>
and R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[209,242,1186,1203]" fontSize="7" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">4+5</subScript>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[138,1009,1242,1266]" box="[138,1009,1242,1266]" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis box="[138,348,1242,1266]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">Abdominal tergites.</emphasis>
Abdominal tergites black; first to third yellow medially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[138,1185,1307,1491]" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis box="[138,322,1307,1331]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Epandrium with 
<emphasis box="[534,558,1307,1330]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">ca</emphasis>
12 setae near posterior margin and at postero-ventral corner (
<figureCitation box="[233,363,1339,1363]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="11.[130,190,853,872]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,817]" captionTargetId="figure-184@11.[170,1128,133,817]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 3. Amiota (Amiota) xishuangbanna Chen and Aotsuka, sp. nov. „ (see Figure 2 for further explanation)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657902/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">Figure 3A</figureCitation>
). Surstylus with 
<emphasis box="[571,595,1339,1362]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">ca</emphasis>
eight prensisetae (
<figureCitation box="[825,953,1339,1363]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="11.[130,190,853,872]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,817]" captionTargetId="figure-184@11.[170,1128,133,817]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 3. Amiota (Amiota) xishuangbanna Chen and Aotsuka, sp. nov. „ (see Figure 2 for further explanation)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657902/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">Figure 3B</figureCitation>
). Paramere acutely curved basally and formed triangular corner in lateral view, with 
<emphasis box="[973,997,1372,1395]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">ca</emphasis>
15–16 sensilla submedially and subapically (
<figureCitation box="[484,612,1403,1427]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="11.[130,190,853,872]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,817]" captionTargetId="figure-184@11.[170,1128,133,817]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 3. Amiota (Amiota) xishuangbanna Chen and Aotsuka, sp. nov. „ (see Figure 2 for further explanation)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657902/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">Figure 3D</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal apodeme less-sclerotized (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="11.[130,190,853,872]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,817]" captionTargetId="figure-184@11.[170,1128,133,817]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 3. Amiota (Amiota) xishuangbanna Chen and Aotsuka, sp. nov. „ (see Figure 2 for further explanation)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657902/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">Figure 3C, D</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme with 
<emphasis box="[495,519,1436,1459]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">ca</emphasis>
five pits on each lateral margin; stalk as long as the apical plate (
<figureCitation box="[211,335,1467,1491]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="11.[130,190,853,872]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,817]" captionTargetId="figure-184@11.[170,1128,133,817]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 3. Amiota (Amiota) xishuangbanna Chen and Aotsuka, sp. nov. „ (see Figure 2 for further explanation)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657902/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">Figure 3E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
